The paper deals with trajectory planning and replanning for microaerial vehicles (MAVs) in dynamic environments. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of occupancy grids and computer vision techniques for environment perception, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of optimization techniques for trajectory planning and the use of B-splines for trajectory representation are also common in control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) research.
